<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 5:17PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN ST. CLAIR COUNTY
THROUGH 600 PM EDT...
At 517 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Algonac, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
New Baltimore, Algonac, Harsens Island, Anchorville, Pearl Beach, and
Fair Haven.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
